---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Section 75 Claim Pack"
  description="A £6.99 download including a template claim letter, evidence checklist, and step-by-step guide for making a Section 75 claim against your credit card provider."
  disclaimer={true}
>
  <article class="prose prose-gray max-w-none">

    <h1>Section 75 Claim Pack</h1>

    <p>
      Banks reject a significant proportion of valid Section 75 claims at first attempt, often because the claimant has not framed their case correctly or has left out key information. This pack gives you the tools to make a well-structured claim from the start, and to respond effectively if the bank pushes back.
    </p>

    <div class="not-prose my-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 p-4 text-sm text-gray-600">
      <p class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">What this product is — and is not</p>
      <p class="mb-1">We are not a claims management company. We do not handle claims, contact banks, negotiate with card providers, or represent customers. We provide general information and downloadable template documents only.</p>
      <p>This website provides general information and templates. It is not legal advice. <a href="/disclaimer/" class="underline hover:text-gray-800">Full disclaimer</a></p>
    </div>

    <h2>What is included</h2>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Template claim letter</strong> for standard Section 75 disputes (non-delivery, faulty goods, not as described).</li>
      <li><strong>Template claim letter</strong> for administration and insolvency cases, where the retailer has ceased trading.</li>
      <li><strong>Evidence checklist</strong> setting out what to gather before writing to your bank, and what to attach to your letter.</li>
      <li><strong>Step-by-step submission guide</strong> covering how to address your claim, what the bank is required to do, and what their response should look like.</li>
      <li><strong>FOS escalation template</strong> for use if the bank rejects your claim or does not respond within eight weeks.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What it costs and how to get it</h2>

    <p>
      The claim pack costs <strong>£6.99</strong> as a one-off download. No subscription. No auto-renewal. You pay once, and the files are yours.
    </p>

    <p>
      Payment is handled by Stripe. After payment, you will receive an email with a download link for a PDF containing all the templates and guides.
    </p>

    <div class="not-prose my-6">
      <a
        href="https://buy.stripe.com/fZucN5cKu1Kf9VK0hwes000"
        class="inline-block rounded bg-gray-900 px-6 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-white hover:bg-gray-700 transition-colors"
      >
        Buy the claim pack for £6.99
      </a>
    </div>

    <h2>Is this legal advice?</h2>

    <p>
      No. The claim pack contains template letters and general guidance, not legal advice for your specific situation. If your case is complex, the amount at stake is large, or you have already been through the Financial Ombudsman process without success, you should consider consulting a solicitor who specialises in consumer law.
    </p>

    <p>
      For most standard Section 75 disputes involving administration, non-delivery, or goods not as described, the templates in this pack are sufficient to make a well-structured claim without professional help.
    </p>

    <h2>Refund policy</h2>

    <p>
      Because this is a digital download, we cannot accept returns once the file has been downloaded. If you experience a technical problem with the download, contact us and we will resolve it promptly.
    </p>

  </article>
</BaseLayout>
